OL,3,C'Intergalactic mystery' of how giant
OL,4,Cgalaxies formed close to being solved
OL,6,FDr Annagrazia Puglisi has said in a
OL,7,Fpaper published, that galaxies
OL,8,F"crashing together" 12 billion years
OL,9,Fago could be the explanation.
OL,11,FShe said: "Two disc galaxies smashing
OL,12,Ftogether caused gas, the fuel from
OL,13,Fwhich stars are formed, to sink
OL,14,Ftowards their centre, generating
OL,15,Ftrillions of new stars.
OL,17,F"These cosmic collisions happened some
OL,18,Feight to 12 billion years ago, when
OL,19,Fthe universe was in a much more active
OL,20,Fphase of its evolution.
OL,1,W~s1x0~s1~s hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}   G2/6
