OL,3,C'Intergalactic mystery' of how giant
OL,4,Cgalaxies formed close to being solved
OL,6,F"These galaxies form quickly ` gas is
OL,7,Fsucked inwards to feed black holes and
OL,8,Ftriggers bursts of stars, which are
OL,9,Fcreated at rates 10 to 100 times
OL,10,Ffaster than our Milky Way."
OL,12,FThe scientists will now combine their
OL,13,Ffindings with data taken from
OL,14,Ftelescopes aboard the James Webb and
OL,15,FEuclid satellites, and the Chinese
OL,16,FSpace Station, to map the stellar
OL,17,Fcomponents of galaxies.
